    "biography": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Grafvitnir, Rot-Given-Shape — Stage 2</strong></p><p><em>Supernatural, Gargantuan • Level 7 Solo • Stamina 200 • Speed 6 • Stability 6 • Free Strike 8 • EV 108</em></p><p>What rises from the roots is not a wolf anymore. Too many joints. Proportions that keep shifting. A face appears in one location and then another. Limbs emerge and dissolve. It is Grafvitnir wearing every shape he’s worn in a thousand years of imprisonment, all at once, unable to choose. It is enormously powerful and deeply wrong.</p><p>Takes 2 turns per round. Has 3 Villain Actions (each once per encounter, max 1 per round).</p>",
      "director": "<p><strong>TACTICAL GUIDANCE — STAGE 2:</strong></p><p>Stage 2 is about managing the clock. Grafvitnir’s <strong>Undying Hunger</strong> regenerates 5 Stamina per turn unless the Ever-Ember is burning in the same zone. The party must keep the flame burning while dealing damage.</p><p><strong>Spectral Instability:</strong> All incoming damage is reduced by 3 (min 1). Tell players after first hit — this is fair, predictable, and represents his shifting mass.</p><p><strong>VA Escalation:</strong> VA1 (Root Eruption) locks heroes down. VA2 (Rot Spread) reshapes the battlefield with difficult terrain. VA3 (Reach and Grasp) isolates a single target with grab + ongoing damage.</p><p><strong>Key Moment:</strong> Söldís restores the flame after Grafvitnir extinguishes it. The Ever-Ember’s restoration triggers the Stage 3 transition.</p><p>Expected duration: 3–4 rounds before Söldís’s act triggers the transition.</p>",
      "languages": []
    },
